other_tests.findings: Mild guarding, non-distended abdomen, tenderness in RLQ and LLQ, most tender in RLQ near McBurney's point. Rovsing's sign negative, Obturator sign negative, Psoas sign positive. Bowel sounds present.

Appendix dilated up to 1.9 cm, fluid-filled with surrounding periappendiceal fat stranding and an appendicolith within the proximal portion. No extraluminal free air, no surrounding free fluid. Other abdominal organs normal.
